
[1]monastical

   MONAS'TICAL, a. [Low L. monasticus; Gr. sole, separate.]

   Pertaining to monasteries, monks and nuns; recluse; secluded from the
   temporal concerns of life and devoted to religion; as a monastic life;
   monastic orders.
